post_text:
More great news for Pikeland families! Per Emergency Relief funds, seven WiFi tours will be installed throughout Pike County to support Remote Learning.

The map below shows where the 7 towers are to be installed. As of today, 4 of the towers are operational. Locations for the operational towers include: Detriot Christian Church, Milton Church, Ackles Market in New Hartford and Baylis Town Hall.

Pikeland students with a school issued chromebooks can automatically connect to WiFi at these locations. The chromebooks are configured for this automatic connections and passwords are not needed.

The District has ordered mobile Hotspots for checkout by Pikeland families. When these resources arrive, students/families indicating a lack of Internet service will be notified.

Attention 6th, 7th, and 8th Grade Parents/Guardians

Good morning!
I am trying to develop scheduled times for 6th through 8th grade chromebook pick up. In order for your child to pick up his/her chromebook, the child must be registered, and the Technology Handbook Acceptance must be marked "yes."
Please register your child as soon as possible, read the technology handbook, and mark the Technology Handbook Acceptance "yes." Once this is done, you will be notified of your child's time to pick up the device. We will be sending messages out Monday and Tuesday.

The IESA has reversed their decision and the fall sports season (Baseball & Softball) is back on.

Baseball Parent meeting will be Monday night:
8th grade parents at 5:00 PM
7th grade parents at 6:00 PM

Softball Parent meeting TBA

An updated physical (Good for 13 months) must be on file before athletes can participate in practice/games.

Please read additional information from the IESA below and in the attachment.

This start date is mandated by the Governor's Office. A copy of that document is available at this link: https://coronavirus.illinois.gov/sfc/servlet.shepherd/document/download/069t000000CyCndAAF?operationContext=S1

Additionally, the IESA Board approved a plan for modified seasons in all remaining IESA sports and activities. https://www.iesa.org/temp/IESAAlternativePlan.pdf

post_text:
Dear PHS Class of 2024,
I have not forgotten about you and the need to begin orienting you to Pittsfield High School. I have been so excited to see how many of you jumped into sports conditioning and look forward to watching you compete and participate as a Pittsfield High School Saukee over the next four years.
We are working on posting some resources for you to review. Also, I have held off moving forward with registration as I was hoping to be able to meet many of you in person to answer your questions before you complete registration. Fortunately, Illinois entered into Phase 4 last week so that I can now schedule groups of 50 together. Sometime after July 4, you will be given an opportunity to sign up with your parents to attend one of several orientation sessions that I will hold.
I hope you are enjoying time with your family this summer. I wish you a wonderful Independence Day holiday week. I am looking forward to seeing you soon!
With Saukee Pride,
Mrs. Greger

Today would have been our Pittsfield High School Art Show. In honor of our PHS Seniors, I created a website showcasing their artworks. We have been blessed with very talented students in the class of 2020!

Dear South School Parents:

We will have a packet pickup on May 1, from 2-6 PM. Please come through the normal drop off lane. We will also have bins set up for the return of packet #3.

Our spring picture composites are supposed to be on their way. Our goal is to pass these out on May 15th when parents return packet #4. You will be able to order these online or by phone. Pictures will be mailed directly to your home.

Kindergarten pre-registration packets can be picked up by preschool parents on May 1st from 2-6 PM. Please return the forms in the self-addressed, stamped, envelope. We will mail packets to incoming kindergarten students from other Pittsfield programs this week. If you are new to Pikeland or have a child that is not in a program, please contact the school at 285-2431 for a pre-registration packet. A kindergarten registration and camp will be held in early August.

Thank you all for your support during these trying times. Stay safe, enjoy your families, and stay #saukeestrong.

Doug Smith
Principal

post_text: Saukee Yearbook desperately needs photos of you and how you are spending your time during the school closure. Are you working on the packets your teachers sent home, getting extra sleep, doing chores, playing video games, getting extra hours at work, babysitting your younger siblings, doing workouts/training at home to stay fit for Spring sports, or something else? We are planning on doing an entire Spring spread on this to make up for lost coverage, so we’ll need a lot of pictures. Please send photos to lshade@pikeland.org or get them to Paige Thometz. They can be cell phone photos, but please make sure they have good lighting and color. If you have a DSLR, we would prefer those, but let’s face it, most cell phones today take amazing photos. PLEASE DO NOT ADD FILTERS! You will get photo credit. Please include who took the photo and explain what is happening in it when you send the picture. Thank you!

post_text: We are sad that the cancellation of school will not allow us to hold our Annual Pikeland Music Boosters Spaghetti Supper. As many of you know, the proceeds from this event help fund the music program in grades 5-12. Ticket sales and leftover tickets should have been turned into music teachers yesterday. Schools will be closed from March 16, 2020, through March 30, 2020. Schools will reopen on March 31, 2020. Once school resumes, the processing of ticket refunds will be in the main offices at PCS and PHS. Bring your ticket(s) to an office to obtain your refund. For those of you who have reached out to us and wish to donate the price of your ticket(s), thank you very much. We are working through this unprecedented event, and we appreciate everyone's patience. If you have any questions or concerns, please email Angie Greger at agreger@pikeland.org.

Information for those attending the funeral of Cody Walston today:

Pikeland CUSD will have two shuttle busses running between PCS and the Assembly of God Church today. The request is to allow church parking to be used by family and those directly involved with the service and leading the procession to the cemetery. Please start by using the front parking lots at PCS. If there becomes a need to use the back parking lot please do not block the loops on the north and south ends or the back lane that leads to the bus lane between PCS and PHS. Please continue to keep the Walston family and our school family in your thoughts and prayers. #LiveLikeCody #SaukeeStrong

post_text: The Pittsfield High School community mournfully acknowledges the passing of one of our students. PHS senior Cody Walston unexpectedly passed away today. It is a terribly sad day for Pittsfield High School and our school family is devastated at the loss of such a fine young man. The thoughts and prayers of the entire Pittsfield High School community go out the Walston family. Cody was an exceptional young man with a tremendous smile and wonderful personality. Cody was a friend to all and a true Saukee through and through. There was no one who worked harder in the classroom or the football field. Cody will be greatly missed by the entire Pittsfield High School family, especially his friends and teammates. As our school community mourns the passing of this amazing young man, we ask the community to please keep the Walston family and our students and staff in their thoughts and prayers in the coming days. Additional counselors will available in our schools this week to meet with students and staff.
